Leandro Almeida da Silva or simply Leandro Almeida (born 14 March 1987 in Belo Horizonte), is a Brazilian central defender. He currently plays for Dynamo Kyiv. Almeida made his professional debut for Atltico-MG in a 11 home draw against Atltico-PR in the Campeonato Brasileiro on 2 June 2006 and scored his first professional goal for Atltico-MG in a 12 away defeat to Figueirense in the Campeonato Brasileiro on 8 September 2007.[1] On 24 June 2009 Leandro Almeida transferred to Dynamo Kyiv.[2] 
